1. Stojim *leđima* okrenut prema vratima. (I'm standing with my back facing the door.)
2. Moram da ustanem *leđima* uz zid. (I have to stand with my back against the wall.)
3. Kada se penjem na planinu, držim se *leđima* uz stenu. (When I climb a mountain, I keep my back against the rock.)
4. Kada sam se okrenuo, video sam da je policajac stajao *leđima* prema meni. (When I turned around, I saw that the police officer was standing with his back to me.)
5. Učiteljica nas je zamolila da sednemo *leđima* prema tabli. (The teacher asked us to sit with our backs to the board.)
6. Uspela sam da ukradem novčanik sa *leđima* jednog muškarca. (I managed to steal a wallet from the back pocket of a man.)
7. Kada se izvinjavate, nemojte da okrećete *leđa* sagovorniku. (When you apologize, don't turn your back on the interlocutor.)
8. Na putu do škole, deca se igraju tako što jedni drugima skaču na *leđa*. (On the way to school, kids play by jumping on each other's backs.)
9. Pogledaj kako taj sportista izvodi skok unazad na *leđima*! (Look how that athlete performs a backward jump on his back!)
10. Uvek se istuširam *leđima* okrenutim prema mlazevima vode. (I always shower with my back facing the water stream.)